# CODEOWNERS — TWO-TIER review routing (Golden Path).
#
# Model: AUTONOMOUS work, HITL control plane.
#   - WORK changes merge on a GREEN gate with no human (the ruleset's
#     required_approving_review_count = 0). The gate is the control — so it must
#     stay deterministic and trustworthy because nothing else gates work.
#   - CONTROL-PLANE changes — the gate's OWN definition (this repo IS the gate
#     engine) — are HITL: a PR touching an owned path below needs a human
#     maintainer's approval (require_code_owner_review). An agent must never be
#     able to weaken the gate that gates it.
#
# Source: tc-pipelines/governance/CODEOWNERS (the canonical Golden Path template).
# There is deliberately NO `* @OWNER` line — a default owner would force review
# on EVERY PR. Own only the control plane.

# ── CI / CD / automation (defines how things build, test, and merge) ─────────
/.github/                    @quanyeomans
/CODEOWNERS                  @quanyeomans
/.github/CODEOWNERS          @quanyeomans

# Dependency-update policy + the bot's review routing: a Dependabot PR touches
# manifests/lockfiles/actions owned below, so it routes to a human owner (the
# `reviewers:` key in dependabot.yml is deprecated by GitHub in favour of this).
/.github/dependabot.yml      @quanyeomans

# ── The gate's definition (what "green" means) ───────────────────────────────
/pyproject.toml              @quanyeomans   # [tool.tc_fitness] gate config + dependency pins
/uv.lock                     @quanyeomans
/.python-version             @quanyeomans
/src/tc_fitness/             @quanyeomans   # the gate engine itself — its rules ARE the control plane

# ── Security / governance / provenance ───────────────────────────────────────
/LICENSE                     @quanyeomans
